Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.35,0:00:18.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,I call it—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.04,0:00:20.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,the Finger-Cutting Guillotine!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.79,0:00:22.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,Guillotine?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.29,0:00:25.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,Each player places a finger in the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.80,0:00:29.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,Then we take turns cutting one of these twenty strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.80,0:00:31.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,All it takes is one string.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.81,0:00:35.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,Just one, and the blade falls... along with your finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.68,0:00:40.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,You don't know which string will be the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.18,0:00:44.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,Whoever pulls their finger out first loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.06,0:00:48.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,It's a game of chicken to see who can leave their finger under the blade the longest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.69,0:00:51.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,Whoever gets cold feet first loses the gamble!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.78,0:00:53.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.87,0:00:56.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,You're free to accept or refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.34,0:00:58.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's no use.{\i0}
